		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Re: Tricky-to-emulate sound stuff from games?</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />It seems a little hard to implement the triangle accidentally wrongly: once you use a 32-step waveform you're already basically right. To get it wrong, I think you'd have to be doing the entire APU wrong. (something like &quot;translate period to pitch, synthesize triangle at PC sample rate&quot;)

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

